race.comment: Sticking with the Victorian visitor TOUCHDOWN (4), who hasn't done much wrong in three starts. This is a nice progression and he'll get every chance to win again with Pannell riding from barrier four. He looks the one to beat. TOWER OF TUSCANY (8) has been runner-up at this track and distance at his two most recent starts. While he doesn't win out of turn, he looks well placed here to fight out the finish. The best Victorian form of CLEITUS (2) gives him a chance here, although his first run for the new stable was only fair. COCKATOO ROSE (9) must be included in quaddies and exotics. She keeps raising the bar and might be able to win again.
